The paper proposes a deep learning-based framework for biomedical literature retrieval, which involves graph-augmented document representation learning, query expansion and representation learning, and learning to rank biomedical articles. The use of graph-based representation and external knowledge sources suggests a focus on information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP), which are subfields of computer science that fall under cs.IR and cs.CL. The use of deep learning models such as BiLSTM and CNN suggests a focus on machine learning (ML), which falls under cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.DL. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR and cs.CL, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.DL.
